{
  "texts": [
    "For weak static fields, σyyy grows linearly with the static field up to |E DC | ≲ 1 mV/Å, whereas components that contain out-of-plane indices remain linear up to approximately |E DC | ≲ 7.5 mV/Å.",
    "For larger fields the response saturates.",
    "The in-plane components exhibit a sharper inflection, whereas the out-ofplane ones saturate more gradually.",
    "The saturation field also depends on photon energy, so different frequencies show different onset values.In this linear regime, the response satisfies σ(2)zyy (ω; E DC) ≈ σ (3)zyyz E DC as expected from the Taylor expansion discussed in Sec.",
    "The derivative with respect to E DC is nearly constant in this range, which confirms the direct link between the induced second-order response and the third-order conductivity."
  ]
}